  "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nGets hibernate entity does not returns entity updated in a previous transaction\r\n\r\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nWe want to update an entity into a transaction and get the updated entity after committing transaction \n\n### Actual behavior\n\nWe update and persist an entity into a transaction, when we get entity outside the same transaction, the entity is not up to date\n\n### How to Reproduce?\n\nrun tests from [https://github.com/resilience-guillaume-gardais/quarkus-transaction-issue](https://github.com/resilience-guillaume-gardais/quarkus-transaction-issue)\n\n### Output of `uname -a` or `ver`\n\nLinux bdl09-dx 6.5.0-14-generic #14-Ubuntu SMP PREEMPT_DYNAMIC Tue Nov 14 14:59:49 UTC 2023 x86_64 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux\n\n### Output of `java -version`\n\nopenjdk version \"21.0.1\" 2023-10-17\n\n### Quarkus version or git rev\n\n3.6.4\n\n### Build tool (ie. output of `mvnw --version` or `gradlew --version`)\n\nGradle 8.1.1\n\n### Additional information\n\n_No response_",
